<div><h3>SCRN 107 - Introduction to Digital Filmmaking </h3>  <p><hr>An introduction to the skills and technology required for digital filmmaking. Each student will conceptualize, design, shoot, and edit three digital film projects (individual and collaborative). The course explores both the art and craft of moving image production; and there is a strong emphasis on the creation of imaginative and personal work.</p>

<p>Students will be charged a V &amp; PA lab fee upon registering for this course.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> AP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every semester<br><br></p></div>		</td>
